The rand firmed against the US dollar on rumours that the ANC will discuss the removal of President Jacob Zuma at a major party meeting. JOHANNESBURG - The rand firmed more than 1.5% against the US dollar on Tuesday on rumours that the African National Congress will discuss the removal of President Jacob Zuma at a major party meeting. An ANC spokesman said the rumours as “complete fabrication”. The rand firmed to 13.0175 per dollar, its firmest since 25 April, according to Thomson Reuters data. By 12.57 GMT, it had retreated to 13.0850/dollar, 1.21% firmer than its overnight close.